<cite class="citation book" about="#mwt85" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book\n","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Khurana"},"first":{"wt":"Rakesh"},"authorlink":{"wt":"Rakesh Khurana"},"title":{"wt":"From Higher Aims to Hired Hands: The Social Transformation of American Business Schools and the Unfulfilled Promise of Management as a Profession"},"url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/books?id=v3DfpKEsNREC"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2013-08-24"},"origyear":{"wt":"2007"},"year":{"wt":"2010"},"publisher":{"wt":"Princeton University Press"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-1-4008-3086-2"},"page":{"wt":"3"},"quote":{"wt":"When salaried managers first appeared in the large corporations of the late nineteenth century, it was not obvious who they were, what they did, or why they should be entrusted with the task of running corporations."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAoM"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Rakesh_Khurana" title="Rakesh Khurana" id="mwAoQ">Khurana, Rakesh</a> (2010) [2007]. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=v3DfpKEsNREC" id="mwAoU"><i id="mwAoY">From Higher Aims to Hired Hands: The Social Transformation of American Business Schools and the Unfulfilled Promise of Management as a Profession</i></a>. Princeton University Press. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAoc"> </span>3. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAog">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAok"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-1-4008-3086-2" title="Special:BookSources/978-1-4008-3086-2" id="mwAoo">978-1-4008-3086-2</a><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwAos">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwAow">2013-08-24</span></span>. <q id="mwAo0">When salaried managers first appeared in the large corporations of the late nineteenth century, it was not obvious who they were, what they did, or why they should be entr